> Bowls are way past "having a moment"—they've become a pillar of our lunches and dinners. Why? It's simple: Everything's better in a bowl! But seriously, the customizable combo of carbs, protein, veggies, and a drizzle of delicious sauce cannot be denied. True to form, this rendition is fully loaded. Buttery, jasmine rice is topped with saucy ground beef and tender carrots. It's all drizzled with a delectable Sriracha mayo, then topped with crispy fried onions and fresh cilantro. One bite will have you totally bowled over.

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Roughly chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Chicken Breast Strips{10%ounce} and a big pinch of @salt{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Shredded Carrots{4%ounce}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, and @Sesame Dressing{1 1/2%ounce}. Cook until carrots are softened, chicken is cooked through, and sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and @Pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Pat chicken dry with paper towels before cooking.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with chicken mixture and any remaining sauce from pan. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Sprinkle with @Crispy Fried Onions{1%unit} and cilantro. Serve.